===Noun===
'''Dari'''

# The name for the [[Persian] language in official papers of Afghanistan. Persian is the official language in [[Iran]], [[Afghanistan]] and [[Tajikistan]] and is spoken by millions more in Uzbekistan and elswhere. In Afghanistan, also Pashto language has gained official status next to Persian in recent decades. Persian functions as the lingua franca throughout Afghanistan.

The linguistic distribution in Afganistan is as follows:

Pashtu (official) 35%, Persian 52%, Turkic languages (primarily Uzbek and Turkmen) 10%, 30 minor languages (primarily Balochi and Pashai) 3%, much bilingualism.

